<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Cylinder Head and Valves -
        Assemble - Install Valve Guides
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010405.2" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Install Valve Guides</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid possible damage to engine, do not hammer or pound valve guides in cylinder head.</para>
            </caution>
            <note>
                <para>Insert each valve guide with large 15&#176; chamfer end down.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate valve guide with clean engine oil.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Chilling valve guide may facilitate installation.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set cylinder head on hydraulic press. Set each valve guide with large 15&#176; chamfer end
                down. Place
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_108.xml" xrefid="t210010405">Valve Guide Installer (ZTSE1943)</hotlnk>
                between valve guide and hydraulic press piston.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Press each valve guide in cylinder head until Valve Guide Installer bottoms against cylinder
                head.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f210010439" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg5/EG5393.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Install valve guide</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Deburr valve guide, after installation with
                <hotlnk document="eges2101_108.xml" xrefid="t210010405">Valve Guide Deburring Tool (ZTSE4393)</hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To avoid possible damage to engine, do not ream valve guide inside after installation. Service
                    valve guides are provided with finished reamed condition.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean each valve guide.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
